<reference id="groupchoice" xml:lang="en-us">
<title><xmlelement>groupchoice</xmlelement></title>
<shortdesc>The <xmlelement>groupchoice</xmlelement> element is part of the subset of elements that
define syntax diagrams in DITA. A group is a logical set of pieces of syntax that go together. A
group choice specifies that the user must make a choice about which part of the syntax to use.
Groups are often nested. <ph conref="apiname.dita#apiname/progdomainelement"/></shortdesc>
